OL,5,Ccoffin'
OL,7,F"Businesses are currently paying rates
OL,8,Fbased on rental levels that reflect
OL,9,Fthe economic and market conditions
OL,10,Fduring the pandemic in October 2021,"
OL,11,Fshe said.
OL,13,F"The majority of non-domestic
OL,14,Fproperties are expected to see little
OL,15,For no change in their rates liability.
OL,17,F"I would encourage ratepayers to go
OL,18,Fonline to review the new valuation to
OL,19,Fbe applied to their property and that
OL,20,Fof similar properties.
