OL,7,FAcross Northern Ireland, retail
OL,8,Fproperty values have increased overall
OL,9,Fby around 9% compared to 2023, with
OL,10,Fstronger growth in Belfast and more
OL,11,Fmoderate uplifts elsewhere.
OL,13,FDuring the previous revaluation, the
OL,14,Fhospitality sector was significantly
OL,15,Fimpacted by the pandemic, resulting in
OL,16,Flower rateable values at the valuation
OL,17,Fdate.
